HEADWORD: Bushido
<hw>Bu"shi`do`</hw> <pr>(b⟦oomac⟧"sh⟦emac⟧`d⟦omac⟧`)</pr>,
<pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Jap. <ets>bu</ets> military + <ets>shi</ets> knight
+ <ets>d⟦omac⟧</ets> way, doctrine, principle.]</ety> <def>The unwritten
code of moral principles regulating the actions of the Japanese
knighthood, or Samurai; the chivalry of Japan.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Unformulated, <qex>Bushido</qex> was and still is the animating
spirit, the motor force of our country.</q> <rj><qau>Inazo
Nitob⟦eacute⟧.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Bushiness</ent>⟦br⟧
